cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DB. 

The paper deals with named entity disambiguation using deep learning techniques, which is a common problem in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also uses graph-based approaches, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Information retrieval (cs.IR) is also relevant as the paper deals with disambiguating entities in text. Finally, the paper uses \wikidata{} as a knowledge base, which is a database-related topic, making cs.DB a possible sub-category as well.
